Catalysis of the reaction -  5-carboxymethyl-2-hydroxymuconate -eq- 5-carboxy-2-oxohept-3-enedioate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  AMP + H(2)O -eq- D-ribose 5-phosphate + adenine.

Catalysis of the reaction -  D-serine -eq- pyruvate + NH3.

Catalysis of the reaction -  DNA containing 3-methyladenine + H2O -eq- DNA with abasic site + 3-methyladenine. This reaction is the hydrolysis of DNA by cleavage of the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the damaged DNA 3-methyladenine and the deoxyribose sugar to remove the 3-methyladenine, leaving an abasic site.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an alkanesulfonate + O2 + FMNH2 -eq- an aldehyde + sulfite + H2O + FMN.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GDP-alpha-D-mannose + H2O -eq- GDP + D-mannose + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + GTP -eq- AMP + guanosine 3'-diphosphate 5'-triphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-tartrate -eq- H(2)O + oxaloacetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-allo-threonine -eq- glycine + acetaldehyde.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-arabinose -eq- L-ribulose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-aspartate + O2 -eq- iminosuccinate + hydrogen peroxide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-carnitine -eq- crotono-betaine + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-fucose -eq- L-fuculose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-fuculose + ATP -eq- L-fuculose 1-phosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-fuculose 1-phosphate -eq- (S)-lactaldehyde + glycerone phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-rhamnose -eq- L-rhamnulose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + L(or D)-ribulose -eq- ADP + L(or D)-ribulose 5-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-ribulose 5-phosphate -eq- D-xylulose 5-phosphate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + L-xylulose -eq- ADP + L-xylulose 5-phosphate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  NADPH + H+ + NAD+ -eq- NADP+ + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-acetylneuraminate -eq- N-acetyl-D-mannosamine + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-ethylmaleimide + 2 H+ -eq- N-ethylsuccinimide.

Catalysis of the reaction -  NADPH + H+ + NAD+ -eq- NADP+ + NADH + H+. The reaction is A-specific (i.e. the pro-R hydrogen is transferred from the 4-position of reduced nicotinamide cofactor) with respect to NAD+ and B-specific (i.e. the pro-S hydrogen is transferred) with respect to NADP+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  FMNH2 + NAD(P)+ -eq- FMN + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NADPH + H+ + acceptor -eq- NADP+ + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  Lipid A-core + colanic acid -eq- MLPS.
Catalysis of the polymerization of o-antigen chains. O-antigens are tetra- and pentasaccharide repeat units of the cell walls of Gram-negative bacteria and are a component of lipopolysaccharide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-succinylbenzoate + ATP + CoA -eq- 2-succinylbenzoyl-CoA + AMP + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the transfer of a methyl group from S-adenosyl-L-methionine to a substrate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H2O + UDP-2,3-bis(3-hydroxymyristoyl)glucosamine -eq- 2,3-bis(3-hydroxymyristoyl)-beta-D-glucosaminyl 1-phosphate + UMP.
Catalysis of the removal of an acetyl group from the 2-N position of glucosamine in the lipid A precursor UDP-3-O-(R-3-hydroxymyristoyl)-N-acetylglucosamine.
